<article>
    <h1>Reel in the week&#xAD;ends!</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200821/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-21"><time>2020-08-21</time></a>
        - <span>CLASSIFIED&#xAD;S</span>
        - <span role="byline">JUSTIN CHUA</span>
    </section>

    <p>The week­end is upon us, and that opens up a world of pos­si­bil­i­ties just wait­ing to be un­cov­ered. A pop­u­lar pas­time for us Sin­ga­pore­ans has to be that of eat­ing, and lucky for us, our coun­try is blessed with a riches of tasty fare stretch­ing across mul­ti­ple cul­tures.</p>
    <p>Fancy some seafood? Then head on over to Tasty Loong by Chef Pung. You might find just what you are look­ing for in their crab seafood combo! Spoil your­self with fresh prawns, green clams, mini lob­ster, mush­room and more! They also serve up de­li­cious crispy ce­real prawns with but­ter eggs!</p>
    <p>If you are after some­thing a lit­tle more plush, then M Ho­tel Sin­ga­pore’s Cafe 2000 may very well en­tice you with their spread. I mean, with an all-you-can-eat free flow of ap­pe­tis­ers, bread, soup and desserts to choose from, what’s there not to cave in to! There’s also 30 per cent off their semi-buf­fet!</p>

